Conclusion: Although neither disc matches my ideal of an original, cohesive early‑1960s studio album, The Very Best of Prince is closer to my priorities — it offers inventive, performance‑driven songwriting and rhythmic detail that reward repeat listening and preserve identifiable artistic craft more effectively than the slick, AOR‑leaning Phil Collins singles compilation.

