- In short: both CDs have vocal‑forward qualities, but the early‑60s remaster is the stronger match to my stated priorities — it explicitly addresses hiss reduction without sacrificing dynamics, emphasizes punch and separation, includes the tight song lengths and harmonies I favor, and offers coherent sequencing. For those reasons I choose the remastered early‑60s LP and reject the Monkees greatest‑hits singles collection.

